Uncertainty About the Company=E2=80=99s Prospects
Sometimes, you=E2=80=99re at a startup and you=E2=80=99re just not sure it=
=E2=80=99s going to work, or how much it=E2=80=99s going to work.=C2=A0
While you=E2=80=99re employed, you=E2=80=99re willing to pay higher taxes i=
n the future so you don=E2=80=99t have to spend your hard-earned money toda=
y on an uncertain bet. They=E2=80=99re called options for a reason.
When you leave, you need to make a hard choice: spend my money to buy these=
 shares now and hope that there=E2=80=99s a good liquidity event in the fut=
ure, or forfeit most of the on-paper comp earned through years of hard work=
=2E It=E2=80=99s never easy to give away=
 those options, and many people just =
buy so that they don=E2=80=99t feel regret if things do go well. But it=E2=
=80=99s expensive.=C2=A0
Sometimes, employees even leave, exercise their options, and then sell when=
 given the opportunity because they think the buyer believes in the company=
 more than they do. If you haven=E2=80=99t listened to my podcast with my f=
riend Brett [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OwyAMhU9TlhUYnCYLFrOZa=
0T8OCkaAhGQqXL7oc1iJMuWZdnP73Om0ZrLqfdcG3unuZ076USvGqk1KuyoVObgtRhglKgm5rXy=
YsSRhTovhWgzIepWDmL7YWNwpoWcPhucA7KnVuIhlJsm7wduSKIZ7QIPcii4HQROl645fKDkSNM=
vlTMnYlE_W9vrTX7d4LtHe4X3R3eXt95ZSzH6QrWGtLKggYPgCkAAouR3cbcwCo4PjwoNB1B2kQ=
vCAsYhB4l0U3xb4V4PW5txP--zrOiUm82ln-zjn6fZKH4G3drc63ak0M6ZkrGR_OW6XfA-HOaVE=
pUO1c-mdWRi4tMg5AAoL5cdS4c4CD4K1pV97lvpX_QP2eSFcA], he was the first employ=
ee at Drizly and sold most of his shares in the secondary market when he go=
t the chance. He thought he was real smart, until Uber recently acquired Dr=
